festival.introText:
The Love Supreme Jazz Festival is a 3 day greenfield jazz festival held in the first weekend of July in the stunning surroundings of Glynde Place in the beautiful South Downs in East Sussex.

It is the first full weekend camping jazz festival in the UK but also welcomes day-trippers and non-camping weekend visitors. The festival is approximately 20 minutes from Brighton and an hour and a half from central London by train or by car.

Love Supreme has 4 stages: The Main Stage which hosts headliners and more contemporary artists with a soul and funk lineage; The Big Top which hosts the cream of international and UK jazz artists; The Arena where you will find younger artists pushing the limits of what jazz, soul and funk is in the present day; and The Bandstand which has the best jazz in East Sussex and Brighton hosted by the Verdict Jazz Club.

DJs and club nights, talks and lectures, panels, classic album playbacks, films, dance classes, kids areas, VIP experiences, camping, and fairground... it’s an immersive musical weekend which has quickly built a loyal and dedicated following.

reviews.title: Review of Love Supreme Festival
reviews.body: Jacksons were awesome, Corinne Bailey-Rae good, Johnny Negro - excellent.  Well organised event, no queues for drinks, plenty of food choice, friendly.

faqs.question: When is Love Supreme Jazz Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: Love Supreme Jazz Festival takes place on Friday 30th June - Sunday 2nd July 2023.

faqs.question: How much are tickets for Love Supreme Festival?
faqs.answer: Please keep an eye on the ticket section for prices.

faqs.question: How to get to Love Supreme Festival?
Where is Love Supreme Jazz Festival?
faqs.answer: Love Supreme Jazz Festival will take place at Glynde Place, Glynde, East Sussex, BN8 6SX.

faqs.question: Are pre-payment plan tickets available?
faqs.answer: No, there aren't any payment plans available for this event.

faqs.question: What are the entry times to Love Supreme Jazz Festival?
faqs.answer:
The campsites will be open from 12pm on Friday 30th June to 12 pm on Monday 3rd July.

 

Festival arena times:

  • Friday 30th June - 3pm (last entry 10pm)
  • Saturday 1st July - 11am (last entry 9pm)
  • Sunday 2nd July - 11am (last entry 9pm)

For the most up-to-date details see https://lovesupremefestival.com/the-essentials/

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Are there any age restrictions at Love Supreme Jazz Festival?
faqs.answer:
Love Supreme Jazz Festival is an all-ages event, however under 16s must be accompanied by an adult aged 18 or over. A maximum of one under 16 can be accompanied by an adult aged 18-20, and four under 16s can be accompanied by an adult aged 21 or over.

 

Proof of age (photo driving/provisional licence / passport / proof of age card with a PASS logo) may be required on entry and all bars operate a strict Challenge 25 Policy.

faqs.question: What can I / can't I bring to Love Supreme Jazz Festival?
faqs.answer: For a full list of what you can and can't bring to Love Supreme Jazz Festival, please see https://lovesupremefestival.com/what-can-i-bring-2/
